SIMPLE: absurdity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Absurdity
<hw>Ab*surd"i*ty</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Absurdities</plw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L. <ets>absurditas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>absurdite</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being absurd or inconsistent with
obvious truth, reason, or sound judgment.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>absurdity</xex> of the actual idea of an infinite number.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is absurd; an absurd action; a logical
contradiction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His travels were full of <qex>absurdities</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Absurdly</ent>⟦br⟧
